Both files are written. Summary of what was found:

**Key result**: The dataset has a single, large biomarker-restricted treatment effect. `feature_016` (the only binary feature with a positive PFS effect) has essentially no impact in most patients (+0.002 mo, p=0.69), but produces a **+4.92-month PFS benefit** (p < 1e-300) in patients meeting the joint eligibility criteria:

- `feature_018 == 1` (positive predictive biomarker)
- `feature_031 == 0` (absence of resistance marker)
- `feature_028 == 0` (small-prevalence resistance marker)
- `feature_005 == 0` (small-prevalence resistance marker)

This subgroup contains 9,013 of 50,000 patients (18%). Final saturated model reaches R² = 0.979.

Other strong (purely prognostic, not treatment) signals: `feature_015` (+0.17/unit, dominant continuous predictor), `feature_014` (-1.10/level), `feature_023` (-1.42), `feature_011` (-0.91), squamous histology (-0.72), current smoking (-0.55 vs former/never), `feature_017` (-0.073/unit), `feature_025` (+0.46/unit). `feature_023` and `feature_011` were ruled out as treatments because their effects are uniformly negative across every stratum.

Outputs:
- `transcript.json` (25 iterations, 28 hypotheses, schema-validated)
- `analysis_summary.txt` (full narrative)
